dcterms:description: A graph where each node represents an image uploaded to Flickr. An undirected edge is drawn between two nodes if the corresponding images share common properties, such as the same geographic location, same gallery, or were commented on by the same user. The node features are 500-dimensional bag-of-words representations of the images.
dcterms:title: Flickr

dcterms:description: An Amazon product co-purchasing network where each node corresponds to an Amazon product, and edges between nodes indicate that the two products are frequently purchased together. The node features are 100-dimensional bag-of-words vectors of the product descriptions.
dcterms:title: ogbn-products

dcterms:description: The friendship graph of a Slovak online social network where nodes represent users, and edges represent directed friendship relations. Node features include profile information such as geographical region, registration time, and age.

dcterms:description: A connected undirected graph representing relationships between accounts on the streaming platform Twitch. Each node represents a Twitch user, and an edge indicates mutual followers. Node features include the number of views, creation and update dates, language, lifetime, and whether the account is dead.
dcterms:title: twitch-gamer
